gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 102, Kings 101
gameRecap.excerpt: Klay Thompson hit a mid-range jumper with .2 seconds left to lift the Warriors over the Kings, 102-101. Stephen Curry recorded 21 points, five rebounds, and three assists for the Warriors, with Dario Saric adding 15 points, six rebounds, and two assists in the victory. Domantas Sabonis tallied 23 points, 11 rebounds, and eight assists for the Kings in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 4-1 on the season, while the Kings fall to 2-2.
